An interactive table of user-defined core genes, with 1st column Genes for gene symbols, 2nd column Weights for gene weights. For example, take as inputs the resulting output from eV2CG.

Output: core and peripheral genes

Manhattan plot illustrates affinity scores for genes that are color-coded by chromosomes, with the top 30 genes labelled. Also provided is an editable PDF file for download.

Figure 1: Manhattan plot illustrating scores (y-axis) for genes (color-coded by chromosomes; x-axis), with top scored genes labelled.

An interactive table of core and peripheral genes, with the column Scores quantifying the affinity to core genes (sum up to 1) and the column Type telling the gene type (either Core for core genes or Peripheral for peripheral genes). Genes are cross-referenced and hyperlinked to GeneCards.
